27 Aug 2011 15:14






First off, I had given this about even odds that it was going to be downvoted to oblivion for being too silly, so having it reach double digits is a pleasant surprise, to say the least. Turns out that trying to describe a magic spell without using either  is hard to do. Also, I wasn't consciously trying to, but I managed to not expunge anything, for whatever it's worth.

moose, I thought about it, and I still want to stay away from using actual DD spell names. I think they would detract more than they'd add, IMO. 'Sides, Robo-Dude has that covered already.

Sal, um. But, you gotta crawl before you can walk, and so I didn't want to make the effects here at all powerful.

Kerlyssa, D some unspecified source. Making it Satanic in nature would have imposed religiosity on it (since Satan is specifically a Judeo-Christian concept) that, frankly, would not have worked at all.

Ker/Eric, I can certainly see how this could be a -J but if I were trying to make it a -J, I would have gone for over the top instead of subdued. As it is, it's right where it belongs (or will be, once it gets its number).

Severe, crap, I had totally forgotten about 433 when I wrote this up. I think mine is different enough from yours to stand on its own, but I can definitely see the similarities.

And as always, thanks to everyone for reading, voting, and commenting.

(That turned out longer than expected. Ah well.)







